<section id="fb0">
  <p align="left">
    <b>1. Employment Opportunities </b>
  </p>
  <p align="left">- More and better job opportunities for locals</p>
  <p align="left">- Tourist industry only offers locals menial, badly-paid, seasonal jobs</p>
  <p align="left">
    <b/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <b>2. Business and the local economy </b>
  </p>
  <p align="left">- Local businesses flourish</p>
  <p align="left">- If holiday company is often foreign-owned, little money may reach local economy</p>
  <p align="left"/>
  <p align="left">
    <b>3. Infrastructure, facilities and the environment</b>
  </p>
  <p align="left">- Tourist facilities may cause environmental damage </p>
  <p align="left">- Locals as well as tourists benefit from improved infrastructure</p>
  <p align="left"/>
  <p align="left">
    <b>4.  Local customs and culture</b>
  </p>
  <p align="left">- Local customs and traditions may not be respected</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">- Locals and tourists learn about each other&#x2019;s cultures</font>
  </p>
